  "why": "The paper's fuzzer (DeepTest) intentionally uses realistic, semantic-preserving image transformations (brightness, contrast, translation, scaling, rotation, blur, rain, fog, etc.) and selects parameter ranges for those transformations, so mutations are designed to preserve plausibility at each individual step. However, DeepTest combines/ stacks transformations iteratively (Algorithm 1) without an explicit mechanism that bounds or measures cumulative distortion relative to the original seed across multiple mutation rounds. The authors apply a post-hoc filter (Equation 3) and only report bugs for transformations whose MSE is close to the original to reduce false positives, but that is a reporting/filtering criterion rather than an explicit, per-iteration control of accumulated perturbation during fuzzing. These behaviors match the metric definition for \"Medium.\"",
